text: Mayes County is a county in the U.S. state of Oklahoma. As of 2020, 39,046 people lived there. Its county seat is Pryor, also known as Pryor Creek. ==Bordering counties== *Craig County (north) *Delaware County (east) *Cherokee County (southeast) *Wagoner County (south) *Rogers County (west) == Cities and towns == *Adair *Ballou *Cedar Crest *Chouteau *Disney *Grand Lake Towne *Hoot Owl *Iron Post *Langley *Locust Grove *Mazie *Murphy *Pensacola *Pin Oak Acres *Pryor Creek *Pump Back *Salina *Sams Corner *Snake Creek *Spavinaw *Sportsmen Acres *Sportsmen Acres Community *Strang *Wickliffe == NRHP Sites == The following sites in Mayes County are listed on the National Register of Historic Places: * Cabin Creek Battlefield, Pensacola * Farmers and Merchants Bank, Chouteau * Lewis Ross/Cherokee Orphan Asylum Springhouse, Salina * Pensacola Dam, Langley * Territorial Commercial District, Chouteau * Union Mission Site, Mazie == References == Category:Oklahoma counties Category:1907 establishments in Oklahoma
